  introContent={`
    <p>Faisalabad Electric Supply Company (FESCO) supplies electricity to over 5.6 million consumers across eight districts of Punjab: <strong>Faisalabad</strong>, <strong>Sargodha</strong>, <strong>Jhang</strong>, <strong>Toba Tek Singh</strong>, <strong>Bhakkar</strong>, <strong>Khushab</strong>, <strong>Mianwali</strong>, and <strong>Chiniot</strong>. Established in 1997, FESCO serves Pakistan's third-largest city and the country's undisputed textile capital — Faisalabad — which hosts hundreds of textile mills, power looms, and garment factories that collectively drive a significant portion of Pakistan's export economy.</p>
    <p>FESCO's territory is an economic engine. <strong>Faisalabad city</strong> alone has more than 400 textile factories and thousands of power looms. The industrial electricity demand from this sector makes FESCO one of Pakistan's highest-revenue DISCOs. Beyond Faisalabad, FESCO covers <strong>Sargodha</strong> (Pakistan's citrus capital), <strong>Jhang</strong> (the City of Saints), <strong>Toba Tek Singh</strong>, <strong>Mianwali</strong>, <strong>Chiniot</strong> (Pakistan's furniture capital), and <strong>Khushab</strong>.</p>
    <p>To check your FESCO bill online, enter your <strong>14-digit FESCO reference number</strong> in the bill checker above. Your reference number is printed at the top of every FESCO electricity bill. You can also use your <strong>10-digit Customer ID</strong> (click Customer ID tab). For SMS-based bill checking, send <em>pitc [14-digit reference number]</em> to <strong>8334</strong> for your bill amount and due date.</p>
    <p>FESCO operates under NEPRA's national tariff. Domestic consumers averaging 200 units or less per month qualify as <strong>Protected</strong> and receive subsidized rates starting from Rs 13.48/unit. Higher consumers are classified as <strong>Unprotected</strong> with rates reaching Rs 48.84/unit for 700+ unit consumers. FESCO bills are typically available online by the 20th to 25th of each month.</p>
    <p>PakistanBill.online is <strong>Pakistan's only platform</strong> covering all 19 utility providers. Alongside this checker, you can also check: <a href="/mepco-bill/">MEPCO bill</a> | <a href="/gepco-bill/">GEPCO bill</a> | <a href="/iesco-bill/">IESCO bill</a> | <a href="/sngpl-bill/">SNGPL gas bill</a> | <a href="/wasa-faisalabad-bill/">WASA Faisalabad</a>. Use our free <a href="/electricity-bill-calculator/">electricity bill calculator</a> to estimate charges before your bill arrives, or visit our <a href="/dashboard/">universal bill dashboard</a> to check multiple bills without switching pages. Also see: <a href="/blog/fesco-reference-number/">How to find your FESCO reference number</a> — and our complete <a href="/faisalabad/">Faisalabad utility bills guide</a>.</p>
  `}

  howToSteps={[
    "Find your 14-digit FESCO reference number — printed in bold at the top-right area of your FESCO electricity bill, near your consumer name.",
    "Open the bill checker tool at the top of this page. Reference Number tab is active by default.",
    "Type your 14-digit FESCO reference number carefully. Enter only numbers — no spaces, dashes, or letters.",
    "Click Check Bill. The tool connects to bill.pitc.com.pk/fescobill and fetches your latest bill from the official PITC server.",
    "Your complete FESCO bill appears in 3 to 5 seconds — showing total due, due date, units consumed, meter readings, and all surcharges.",
    "Click Download PDF to save your bill as PDF, or click Print for an immediate paper duplicate."
  ]}

  billReadingTips={[
    "Your FESCO reference number is permanent — save it in your phone. You need it every month to check your bill without searching for a paper copy.",
    "The Category on your FESCO bill determines your rate. D-Protected means subsidized rates for low consumers. D-Unprotected means full slab rates. Industrial consumers see I-1, I-2, or C-1 for commercial.",
    "Faisalabad textile consumers with industrial connections should monitor Maximum Demand (MD) charges. MD penalties apply when actual peak demand exceeds your sanctioned load — a common cause of high industrial FESCO bills.",
    "If your bill says Estimated instead of Actual, FESCO's meter reader did not visit your premises. Request an actual reading by calling 118 — estimated bills often cause large catch-up charges the following month.",
    "Review your bill's Arrears line. If you see arrears you believe you paid, bring your payment receipts to your nearest FESCO sub-division office for manual clearance.",
    "The FPA (Fuel Price Adjustment) charge varies every month. In winter it is typically higher because expensive thermal plants compensate for reduced hydro generation.",
  ]}

  savingTips={[
    "Faisalabad textile factory owners: shift power loom and production operations to off-peak hours (before 6:30 PM and after 10:30 PM) to reduce demand charges and per-unit costs significantly.",
    "Residential consumers in Faisalabad: Chiniot, Jhang, and Sargodha have milder climates than Lahore — use fans for the maximum possible months before turning on AC to stay under the 200-unit Protected threshold.",
    "Sargodha citrus orchard owners using electric tube wells should install timers to run pumps at night (off-peak). This reduces both FESCO peak-hour charges and extends pump motor life.",
    "FESCO net metering is available for solar panel owners. Apply at fesco.com.pk or at your nearest FESCO division office. Faisalabad's annual solar irradiance is excellent — rooftop solar can offset 70–80% of textile factory electricity consumption.",
    "Replace fluorescent lighting in your factory or home with LED lighting. A Faisalabad power loom workshop replacing 50 tube lights (40W each) with LEDs (18W each) saves approximately 660 units per 10-hour shift — Rs 25,000+ per month at industrial rates.",
    "Set AC units in your home or office to 26°C. In Faisalabad's extreme summer heat, ACs running at 20°C instead of 26°C can add 200–300 extra units to your monthly bill.",
  ]}

  complaintProcess={[
    "Call FESCO helpline 118 or toll-free 0800-66554 with your reference number. Explain the billing issue and get a Complaint Registration Number (CRN).",
    "Visit your nearest FESCO sub-division office in Faisalabad, Sargodha, Jhang, or your district for issues requiring document review or meter inspection.",
    "FESCO must resolve billing complaints within 14 working days under NEPRA Consumer Protection Regulations. Track your complaint using the CRN.",
    "Escalate to NEPRA at 0800-63000 (toll-free) if FESCO ignores your complaint beyond 14 working days. File at nepra.org.pk with your CRN as evidence.",
    "For persistent ignoring, escalate to Wafaqi Mohtasib (Federal Ombudsman) at mohtasib.gov.pk — this is a legally binding free service that forces FESCO to respond.",
  ]}

