  faqs={[
    { question: "How do I check my FESCO bill online in March 2026?", answer: "Enter your 14-digit FESCO reference number in the bill checker above and click Check Bill. Your complete FESCO electricity bill for March 2026 appears in seconds — amount due, due date, units consumed, and all charges. Free, no login, 24/7." },
    { question: "Where is the FESCO reference number on my bill?", answer: "Your 14-digit FESCO reference number is printed in bold at the top-right area of your electricity bill, near your consumer name and address. It is also on the tear-off payment stub. It is permanent — save it in your phone." },
    { question: "How do I check FESCO bill via SMS?", answer: "Type pitc followed by a space and your 14-digit FESCO reference number, then send to 8334. You receive your bill amount, due date, and units consumed as an SMS reply within seconds. Example: pitc 12345678901234 → send to 8334." },
    { question: "Can industrial consumers in Faisalabad check their FESCO bill online?", answer: "Yes. All FESCO connections — domestic, commercial, and industrial — use the same 14-digit reference number system. Enter your industrial connection reference number in the checker above. Industrial bills are typically larger and contain additional fields for Maximum Demand (MD) charges and load factor details." },
    { question: "How do I download my FESCO duplicate bill as PDF?", answer: "After the bill loads, click Download PDF. Select Save as PDF in the browser print dialog and click Save. Your FESCO duplicate bill downloads instantly as a PDF — ready to share on WhatsApp or print at any shop in Faisalabad or your city." },
    { question: "Why is my FESCO bill high in summer?", answer: "Faisalabad summers are extremely hot. AC units running 12–16 hours daily in June, July, and August easily add 300–500 extra units to your FESCO bill. This often pushes consumers from Protected to Unprotected status, dramatically increasing their per-unit rate. High summer FPA charges set by NEPRA also add Rs 100–300 to bills at peak summer." },
    { question: "How do I pay my FESCO bill online?", answer: "Pay through JazzCash, Easypaisa, or any bank app. Select Electricity, choose FESCO or WAPDA, enter your 14-digit reference number, verify the amount, and confirm. You receive instant SMS confirmation. Payment reflects on FESCO systems within 2 to 4 hours." },
    { question: "What is the FESCO grace period?", answer: "FESCO gives 7 days after the due date to pay without a late payment surcharge. After 7 days, a 10% surcharge applies to the full unpaid amount. Pay on or before your due date to avoid this penalty." },
    { question: "How do I check the FESCO load shedding schedule for Faisalabad?", answer: "Visit ccms.pitc.com.pk and enter your 14-digit FESCO reference number. Your specific feeder's load shedding schedule appears — showing daily OFF slots for your area. Faisalabad city typically experiences 4–8 hours of load shedding; rural areas in Sargodha and Mianwali districts may face more." },
    { question: "Which districts does FESCO serve?", answer: "FESCO covers 8 districts: Faisalabad, Sargodha, Jhang, Toba Tek Singh, Bhakkar, Khushab, Mianwali, and Chiniot. The company serves 5.6 million consumers including Pakistan's largest textile industry concentration in Faisalabad and Chiniot's world-famous furniture manufacturing cluster." },
    { question: "How do I file a billing complaint with FESCO?", answer: "Call 118 or 0800-66554 with your reference number ready. Describe the issue and get a Complaint Registration Number (CRN). FESCO must resolve within 14 working days. Escalate to NEPRA at 0800-63000 if ignored." },
  ]}

